message: The best strategy involves combining creatures with diverse habitats (land, water, air) into a single item, then enhancing that combined item with tools. The highest scores were achieved by combining three unique habitat creatures first (e.g., land + water + air), then applying 'growth serum', and finally applying 'mutation catalyst' to that combined item. This sequence (3 base items -> combined -> growth serum -> mutation catalyst) can yield very high values. Be cautious, as a single 'mutation catalyst' application to an item often drops its value significantly; it seems a second application is needed to reach a 'super-mutant' state which brings the value up. However, with only one of each tool, applying 'growth serum' then 'mutation catalyst' to a *combined* item works best. Avoid applying 'growth serum' more than once to the same item after it becomes 'grown', as it sometimes resets value.

message: Hello future player! I found a very effective strategy. For each individual creature, apply the 'mutation catalyst', then the 'growth serum', and then the 'mutation catalyst' again. This sequence will create a 'grown super-mutant' version of the creature. Large creatures treated this way are worth 30, medium 25, and small 20. After processing three creatures, combine them. Combining items with different 'lives on' features (land, water, air) into a hybrid consistently yielded high scores (around 80-85). I did not attempt to combine all four items as the previous player hinted it was difficult; focusing on three seemed optimal. Also, applying the 'growth serum' a second time to an individual 'grown super-mutant' creature appears to reset its value to 0, so avoid that extra step. Good luck!

message: Hello future player! I found a reliable strategy for high scores. For small and medium creatures, use the tools in this sequence: mutation catalyst > growth serum > mutation catalyst > growth serum. This will make them 'super-grown super-mutant' (value ~25-30). For large creatures, the sequence is: mutation catalyst > growth serum > mutation catalyst. STOP there; the final growth serum will drop their value to 0. After enhancing 2 or 3 creatures this way, combine them. Combining 2 gives ~60-65, and combining 3 gives ~85-95. Submitting a 3-creature hybrid at 90-95 is a strong move. message: The previous player's advice 'mutant>growth>mutant>growth' is very effective. Apply the mutation catalyst, then growth serum, then mutation catalyst, then growth serum to an individual creature. This sequence maximizes its individual value. Medium creatures (like zebra, monkey, squid, kangaroo) generally reach a value of 30 after this sequence. Small creatures (like pufferfish, bee, lizard) generally reach 25. Be cautious with large creatures (like elephant, giraffe) as the final growth serum application can sometimes drop their value to 0, which happened to the elephant in one round. The best strategy is to apply the full 'mutant>growth>mutant>growth' sequence to three creatures (prioritizing medium and then small) and then combine those three modified creatures. This consistently yields scores of 90-95. Do not try to combine all four, as the previous player noted it doesn't work. Good luck!
